grade: Jōyō kanji, taught in junior high
on reading compounds: 膳【ゼン】small dining table (usu. for a single person), serving tray (with legs), meal, food, serving, counter for bowlfuls of rice, counter for pairs of chopsticks
膳越し【ゼンゴシ】rudely reaching over one's serving tray to grab food behind it with one's chopsticks
大膳【ダイゼン】black-bellied plover, grey plover (Pluvialis squatarola)
配膳【ハイゼン】setting a place, setting the table
